org.fluidity.composition.spi

Class EmptyPackageBindings

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fluidity.composition.spi.EmptyPackageBindings
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ComponentContainer.Bindings, PackageBindings

    public abstract class EmptyPackageBindings
extends Object
implements PackageBindings
    Empty package bindings to simplify creation of actual implementations. You don't normally need to implement PackageBindings yourself but when you do, this abstract implementation will give you empty implementations for all methods so that you don't have to.

    Usage

     @SuppressWarnings("UnusedDeclaration")
 final class MyCustomBindings extends EmptyPackageBindings {

   @Override
   public void bindComponents(final ComponentContainer.Registry registry) {
     …
   }

   @Override
   public void initialize(final ComponentContainer container, final ContainerTermination shutdown) {
     …
   }
 }

      • initialize

        public void initialize(OpenContainer container,
                       ContainerTermination shutdown)
                throws Exception
        Perform package initialization if necessary. This method is invoked once after the ComponentContainer.Bindings.bindComponents() method of all PackageBindings objects have been invoked and before any component is externally accessed in the provided container.

        This implementation does nothing; allows subclasses to do nothing by not overriding this method.

        Specified by:
        initialize in interface PackageBindings
        Parameters:
        container - the container that was populated by the ComponentContainer.Bindings.bindComponents(org.fluidity.composition.ComponentContainer.Registry) method.
        shutdown - allows registration of actions to be performed when the container shuts down.
        Throws:
        Exception - when an error occurs.
